From 8eb4d351e90aeb7b067d2f4467d28093496e56a8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 11:59:37 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] QC send-back: send a unit to any earlier active stage,
 not just one step

moveBack() only ever moved a unit exactly one stage back - not enough
for "QC sends it back to Fabrication" when QC sits several stages
later in the sequence. Also loosened GET /workflow-stages from
config:manage to just authentication - a QC user picking a target
department for send-back needs to see the stage list, and they won't
generally hold full admin config permissions; stage names aren't
sensitive, create/update/delete/reorder still require config:manage.

New POST /units/:id/workflow/send-back - takes an explicit target
stage id and a REQUIRED reason (not optional, unlike moveBack's), only
allows targets earlier in the sequence than the current stage, checked
against the current stage's own required permission (same authorization
model as moveBack - it's QC's own clearance that matters, not the
target department's). Logged distinctly on the activity timeline with
both the reason and which stage it came from.

New Send Back panel on the unit detail page, available to anyone
(not gated behind admin) - a stage picker plus a required reason field.
