From d2f04c8fe5286ef3a2d114e85dfe1ee7ed48f157 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 11:59:46 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] Add Rework and Shipment tracking

Rework: deliberately NOT built on the workflow engine - a completed
unit is never reopened (this project's own explicit rule), so
post-shipment rework can't be "move the unit backward." Instead it's
its own linked record: what's wrong, who's assigned, Open/Completed
status, notes, completed/reshipped dates. No internal stages of its
own on purpose - the person doing the fix might be pulled from any
department, there's no fixed sequence to enforce the way there is for
normal production. New rework:manage permission, granted to Supervisor.

Shipment: carrier, ship date, truck number, tracking/BOL number,
driver name, destination-confirmed flag, received-by signature, notes.
One-to-many per unit (not one-to-one) - a reship after rework gets its
own new record, not an edited version of the first shipment, so there's
a real history of every time a unit actually left the building. New
shipment:manage permission, granted to Supervisor.

Both log to the activity timeline (ReworkCreated/ReworkCompleted/
ShipmentLogged) and follow the same access pattern as Comments: the
read-only history is visible to anyone who can view the unit, only the
create/edit actions are gated behind the respective manage permission -
found and fixed this during review, since my first pass had gated the
entire card (including read-only history) behind the manage permission,
which would've hidden shipment/rework status from anyone without it,
inconsistent with how every other unit-detail section already works.
